# Prisma & PostgreSQL

> Performance rules: see `performance.mdc`.
> Repository layer rules: see `architecture.mdc`.

## Prisma Client

- Prefer Prisma Client API over `$queryRaw` / `$executeRaw`
- Use raw SQL only when Prisma Client cannot express the query — document why
- All queries must be type-safe — no untyped raw results

```ts
// ✅
await this.prisma.todo.findMany({ where: { userId } });

// ❌ — unless Prisma Client cannot do it
await this.prisma.$queryRaw`SELECT * FROM todos`;
```

## Repository

Repository rules (data access only, no business logic, Prisma isolated) — see `architecture.mdc` — **Repository Rules** and **Layer Responsibilities**.

Use `select` to fetch only required fields instead of loading full records.

## Schema Changes

- All schema changes go through **Prisma Migrate** — never alter the database manually
- Migration files are committed to `packages/database/prisma/migrations/`
- Run `yarn db:migrate` in development; migrations run in CI/CD for other environments

## PostgreSQL

- Use pagination for all list endpoints (`skip` / `take` or cursor-based)
- Do not `SELECT *` equivalent — use Prisma `select` or `include` intentionally
- Add database indexes for frequently filtered or sorted columns
- Review query plans when adding indexes or complex queries

```ts
// ✅ paginated, selected fields
await this.prisma.todo.findMany({
  where: { userId },
  select: { id: true, title: true, completed: true },
  skip: (page - 1) * pageSize,
  take: pageSize,
});
```
